The paper focuses on deep neural network compression and specifically on weight and activation binarization, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method aims to improve the accuracy of binary neural networks, which is a topic of interest in neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and deep learning (cs.DL).
